    "Optimization on Manifolds.",
    "Riemannian optimization generalizes gradient methods to smooth manifolds (Absil et al., 2008; Bonnabel, 2013; Boumal, 2023) and has proven useful in scenarios such as matrix completion (Vandereycken, 2013) and eigenvalue problems (Edelman et al., 1998).",
    "Despite the theoretical appeal, such methods are rarely applied in large-scale settings, as expensive retraction operations are required to ensure the feasibility of iterates.",
    "Ablin and Peyré (2022) propose an infeasible method for optimization on the orthogonal manifold that does not require retractions.",
    "Rather than ensuring the feasibility of all iterates, the specifically designed landing field guarantees convergence to the manifold in the limit."
  ],
